I don't follow.  I wasn't saying that EverQuest should be used to replace live, face-to-face, social interaction.  I was saying that the negative side effects of these interactions would impact people less in EverQuest than in the real world because of it's anonymous nature which allows people to more easily disassociate themselves from the person on the &quot;other side of the screen&quot; (re: the Flameboard).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Now, I will offer comparison. I have recently been using online PS2 (specifically Tribes). I have found online ps2 very regenerative and non-adictive to my personality type. I can come home, play a 30 min game, go do other stuff, leave...etc. No negative effect. In fact, I have found it to be very healthy and stress relieving--works great for getting those drive home kinks out lol. I did not find that to be the case what so ever with EQ. It was extremely stress inducing and adictive, almost intoxicating.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Is there a way to communicate with people across the Playstation 2 easily like with EverQuest?  I don't own a PS2 yet, but if the answer is &quot;No&quot; I would imagine that is part of why you don't find the game so immersive.  People can and do form very strong social bonds through EverQuest, and as has been mentioned, this is one of the primary reasons (I believe) everyone plays the game so long.  EverQuest is the only game I've ever stuck with for 2.5 years, and the number one reason was the people.  Look at how many people stop playing the game but continue to participate in the community.  However, that doesn't mean it is addictive.  People can and do form the same kind of bonds in school, in chat rooms, at work, over message boards, over the telephone, in sports, at the local bar, etc. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uhayzen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hayzen</A> at: 10/19/02 6:50:19 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utidaljade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tidaljade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bump</span><br>  Posts: 1011<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/19/02 7:08:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rigadoon</span><hr size=1> What else is the game supposed to be used for? I'm confused.&quot;-Hayz<br>
