<br>
However, I believe you are wrong on EQ. EQ has addictive qualities <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> by design</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, because VI needs people to keep playing in order for EQ to make money. Using the random reward schedule technique is one way of accompishing this as is having an, for all practical purposes, endless amount of equipment to upgrade to.<br>
<br>
Throw in the social structure and pressure of keeping up (by time vested in your character) which is heavily influenced by EQs design, and you definatly have a game who relies on a pretty extensive bag of tricks to keep people playing.<br>
<br>
So while I agree that people can and do become addicted to activities/things with no addictive qualities, I don't believe EQ is one of them. EQ is addictive by design imo. <p><br>
