<br>
This has been an industry standard of RPG game design since as long as I can remember.  EverQuest is an <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> obvious</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> rip off of Dungeons &amp; Dragons and The Forgotten Realms universe.  There are many examples I could list to support this claim, but I don't want to string this off-topic again.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, the point is that I don't think this was a design made with the intention of making the game addictive.  It was made this way because games it is based off of have been made this way.  Brad McQuaid has said many times that he and the designers of the game were MUDers and RPGers, and they wanted to recreate that experience.<br>
<br>
Creating a compelling, and enjoyable game is not the same thing as creating an addictive game.  One of the marks of addiction is that you are compelled to keep using the substane, or repeating the action, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> even when you don't want to</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  I don't think anyone here could make the claim that people, would be playing this game if it weren't enjoyable.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Throw in the social structure and pressure of keeping up (by time vested in your character) which is heavily influenced by EQs design, and you definatly have a game who relies on a pretty extensive bag of tricks to keep people playing.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You can find this same thing in real life social groups, work being one of them.  People do get addicted to work, but work is not addictive. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uladmovonwallace.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ladmovonwallace</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Poop... it's what's for dinner.</span><br>  Posts: 1919<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/19/02 10:00:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.send4fun.com/IMAGES/bassethound_playingbanjo_lg_clr.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EverQuest and Addiction</span><hr size=1> of for fucksake you know eq is addictive verant has probally researched this and did all they could to lure people in, its the only way they make $$ if u could win the game then u would not pay every month for it.. i have 0 doubt they took steps to insure they could suck people in and keep them in .. dont bullshit yourself<br>
